<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause xmlns:xt="urn:xpressauthor:trackchanges" id="_b4f52947-629b-4c1b-a356-af9920e339b0" outputclass="ncc-clause"><meta><facet building="Class 2"/><facet building="Class 3"/><facet building="Class 4"/><facet building="Class 5"/><facet building="Class 6"/><facet building="Class 7a"/><facet building="Class 7b"/><facet building="Class 8"/><facet building="Class 9a"/><facet building="Class 9b"/><facet building="Class 9c"/><facet climate="Climate zone 8"/></meta><sptc>5.6.8</sptc><title id="_3eb377c9-91a9-4202-9eaa-de78853a3618">Vertical articulation joints</title><archive-num>2019: 3.3.5.13</archive-num><subclause id="_ca2ef9b1-731c-46f9-862d-0fbfbd5750f0" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_d78cf6a9-1d2a-4e38-81d2-06a5c0f49fd9">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>Vertical articulation joints must be provided in masonry walls in accordance with (2), except in walls constructed on <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1463_0.4.0.xml#_fb3536f6-7ee5-4a29-a4da-402a8e1168dc" id="_56254fa5-3675-4f9f-b101-bc12162020ad" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">sites</xref> where the soil classification is A or S (see <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/4607_0.11.0.xml#_cb39f9fa-321a-430a-bfa1-baff58aaedfb" id="_7a721e44-6f66-4079-8dd6-622a81a98432" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="ncc-clause">4.2.2</xref>).</p></subclause><subclause id="_8e05bbb6-826f-4dc7-a4fc-7f751af82201" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_55d683a4-b7c4-45e5-af75-99763da682c8">SubClause</title><num>2</num><p>Articulation joints between masonry elements must have a width of not less than 10 mm and be provided (see <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/580_0.10.0.xml#_054116e7-8808-4d07-b938-32fedd05381b" id="_1a6fcc9f-8a1d-483f-a70e-f7db888644d2" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">Figures 5.6.8a</xref> and <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/594_0.14.0.xml#_75798bd1-1338-46dd-a73f-be500f05aa76" id="_bddc1602-37c9-409d-b8e0-5dda8deb2dd2" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">5.6.8b</xref>)—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_94ae960c-7516-4370-9de4-4a197348a95d">in straight, continuous walls <xt:insText xt:action="start" xt:author="Jerome Samuel" xt:dateTime="2024-02-23T11:52:00" xt:id="411708f8-534b-41c8-95d5-6a94631c12a3"/>without openings or<xt:insText xt:action="end" xt:id="411708f8-534b-41c8-95d5-6a94631c12a3"/> with openings<xt:delText xt:action="start" xt:author="Jerome Samuel" xt:dateTime="2024-02-23T11:52:00" xt:id="3e9a5dab-3157-4abe-a73b-45af775f700d"/> less than<xt:delText xt:action="end" xt:id="3e9a5dab-3157-4abe-a73b-45af775f700d"/><xt:insText xt:action="start" xt:author="Jerome Samuel" xt:dateTime="2024-02-23T11:52:00" xt:id="86cd6ff1-1bf2-4ef8-bed7-251af5ca5680"/>not more than<xt:insText xt:action="end" xt:id="86cd6ff1-1bf2-4ef8-bed7-251af5ca5680"/> 900 mm x 900 mm<xt:delText xt:action="start" xt:author="Jerome Samuel" xt:dateTime="2024-02-23T11:52:00" xt:id="b5482bf0-1be5-4651-8f2e-ff6d24f2e1e8"/> or walls without openings<xt:delText xt:action="end" xt:id="b5482bf0-1be5-4651-8f2e-ff6d24f2e1e8"/> — at not more than 6 m centres and within 4.5 m, but not closer than 470 mm<xt:insText xt:action="start" xt:author="Jerome Samuel" xt:dateTime="2024-02-23T11:53:00" xt:id="170977ff-0e2c-4269-b952-63f4078d24b7"/>,<xt:insText xt:action="end" xt:id="170977ff-0e2c-4269-b952-63f4078d24b7"/> of all corners; and</li><li id="_8a158df5-c621-426b-8748-5c89eb79fe9d">in straight, continuous walls with openings more than 900 mm x 900 mm — at not more than 5 m centres and located so that they are not more than 1.2 m away from openings; and</li><li id="_b1309cab-9b58-441a-99b0-177ece6dd10b">where the height of the wall changes by more than 20% — at the position of change in height; and</li><li id="_34f30895-4562-48fe-a15c-453a4e64bc06">where a wall changes in thickness; and</li><li id="_fd556481-ed80-4e99-8894-f397861f31e4">at control or construction joints in footings or slabs; and</li><li id="_0e74ee4b-0705-49bb-9f49-367688623e56">at junctions of walls constructed of different masonry materials.</li></ol></subclause><subclause id="_39ed4372-8349-46a7-8086-f73ba29de082" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_4e7c666d-4e37-4bb9-bb4d-3501b38acc8a">SubClause</title><num>3</num><p>Articulation joints must not be located adjacent to arched openings.</p></subclause><subclause id="_15d0c50b-63e0-4571-a488-0fe2d78392e6" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_d5a9997b-72f7-426c-bdb0-9cdc4ac3f8c0">SubClause</title><num>4</num><p>Articulation joints must be filled with flexible sealant that is supported during installation by—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_1ec3c401-e19c-4b38-a721-1a96bfa332db">a compressible foam or polystyrene filler (see <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/604_0.12.0.xml#_b113ccb0-635b-449c-8312-1065256950c3" id="_62c9f47d-517b-48ca-94f3-ada08ef69a3f" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">Figures 5.6.8d</xref> and <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/4918_0.8.0.xml#_659f2e62-eac9-4166-b9a9-a7a82cf54c3a" id="_b81eed3e-501d-4970-8e18-fab6cab9673e" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">5.6.8e</xref>); or</li><li id="_29299b04-7811-4e28-9827-1a28715248da">a purpose made backer rod (see <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/599_0.14.0.xml#_9dd8ca0e-75be-4f25-b4d4-ef465a8467ec" id="_5973c8bb-dd8f-44aa-bb40-4908f4a78d7c" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">Figures 5.6.8c</xref>, <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/604_0.12.0.xml#_b113ccb0-635b-449c-8312-1065256950c3" id="_49c9b789-47e0-4563-8cbe-41a355f01820" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">5.6.8d</xref>, <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/4918_0.8.0.xml#_659f2e62-eac9-4166-b9a9-a7a82cf54c3a" id="_27659461-929e-486b-ba84-bd9e0a119448" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">5.6.8e</xref> and <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/4919_0.8.0.xml#_49e30a4c-1926-4383-8641-42e561af3b03" id="_5437b806-d280-413b-b23f-2415c2a98629" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">5.6.8f</xref>).</li></ol></subclause><image-reference conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/580_0.10.0.xml" id="_054116e7-8808-4d07-b938-32fedd05381b"><num/><title id="_fc39d29c-a40e-4f63-b555-47282615e80d"/></image-reference><image-reference conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/594_0.14.0.xml" id="_75798bd1-1338-46dd-a73f-be500f05aa76"><num/><title id="_450fba06-3ae1-48b8-8b50-46f57d6552bc"/></image-reference><image-reference conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/599_0.14.0.xml" id="_9dd8ca0e-75be-4f25-b4d4-ef465a8467ec"><num/><title id="_3edb8112-b048-4821-9b8d-0c1c7a5a325c"/></image-reference><image-reference conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/604_0.12.0.xml" id="_b113ccb0-635b-449c-8312-1065256950c3"><num/><title id="_f1c71d37-a8f7-452d-930a-32851dbff4c6"/></image-reference><image-reference conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/4918_0.8.0.xml" id="_659f2e62-eac9-4166-b9a9-a7a82cf54c3a"><num/><title id="_08532ee0-7713-43c5-b1f0-906ea36804a1"/></image-reference><image-reference conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/4919_0.8.0.xml" id="_49e30a4c-1926-4383-8641-42e561af3b03"><num/><title id="_430f4695-87a8-40c3-93f7-4b15dd3a5a62"/></image-reference><callout id="_17ef6795-c496-4c46-a565-4a284de048b2"><callout-type ncc-info-type="info"/><p>For the purposes of 5.6.8, the vertical articulation joint also performs the function of a contraction or expansion joint.</p></callout></clause>